The paper proposes a scalable Gaussian process framework for wireless traffic prediction in cloud radio access networks (C-RANs). This involves hyper-parameter optimization using the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) for parallel processing, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with network management and optimization, which is related to computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The proposed architecture for wireless prediction is a system-level design, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses probabilistic models and cross-validation techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
